Croatia is “seriously considering”
the sale of insurance company  Croatia Osiguranje d.d. (CROSRA)  and
 Hrvatska Postanska Banka d.d. (HPBRA) , Zagreb-based  Globus  reported
today, citing an interview with Finance Minister Slavko Linic.  To contact the reporter responsible for the story: Jasmina
Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for the story: James M. Gomez
at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  